description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a ward clerk to cover for our current ward clerk on maternity leave, in our busy yet exciting Trauma and Orthopaedic department at Basingstoke and North Hampshire Hospital, to be based on D3.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care for patients with a wide range of orthopaedic conditions who are within the department. The post holder will need to be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills, be customer focused and have a positive attitude. In addition, they require an excellent telephone manner, good organisational and IT skills with the ability to handle a variety of tasks under pressure. The successful applicant will undertake reception and general office duties but must also be able to deal sympathetically and appropriately with patients and relatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to know more please get in touch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lenon Mashingaidze, Clinical Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01256 313530&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kim Edney, Ward Managers Assistant&lt;/p&gt;
